<h1 id="abstract">Abstract</h1>

<p>What could go possibly wrong when designing APIs? Everything.
Among many other things, API Design may be inconsistent with pre-existing elements, may be bugged, may not fulfill needs, may be hard to understand or use, may be too specific and impossible to reuse, â€¦</p>

<p>Whatever the organizationâ€™s size, the type of APIs and the designers skills and experience, something will go wrong. That is why, any API design must be reviewed.</p>

<p>During this session, I uncover everything you need to start reviewing the designs of your organizationâ€™s APIs.</p>

<p>Explore subterranean needs! Plunder hoards of inconsistency! Battle legendary design flaws!</p>

<p>The API Design Reviewerâ€™s Starter Set is your gateway to exhaustive and constructive API design reviews. This session contains the essential rules of design reviews plus a few tips and trick that will be of great help on your perilous adventures in the API world.</p>

